<html>
<head>
<title>E-Mail Congresssman Sanford -- SBSC</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="FFFFFF">

<p>

You can use this form to send a letter to Congressman Sanford concerning the Citizens Congress Act. A letter has already been prepared for you, but please customize it to fit your needs. Remember to sign the letter!<p>

Here is Congressman Sanford's email address if you want to send additional comments:
<a href="mailto:sanford@hr.house.gov">sanford@hr.house.gov</a>

<p>
<form action="/townhall/scripts/sbsc-email.cgi" method="post">
Your email address:<br>
<input type="text" size="60" name="a-email">
<p>
The subject of your email:<br>
<input type="text" size="60" name="b-subj" value="Citizen Congress Act">
<p>
Your message:<br>
<textarea cols="60" rows="10" wrap="physical" name="c-text">
Dear Representative 

After years of empty rhetoric, I am glad to see true reform 
brewing in Congress.  I look forward to the day when 
Congress reforms itself via the Citizen Congress Act.

If passed, an initiative such as the Citizen Congress Act 
will help restore my faith in elected officials.  For too 
long, we have been made promises while important measures 
such as term limits and a Balanced Budget Amendment have 
not materialized.

By eliminating perks and wasteful practices from within, 
Congress can begin to reverse the hollow promises of the 
past several years. Abolishment of the federal pension 
system, elimination of franked mass mailings, non-automatic
pay increases, and reduced military aircraft travel are 
significant reforms which also reduce government spending. 
At a time when the country's budget is in poor fiscal 
condition, there is little reason not to tighten the belt 
of Congress.

I was disappointed to see term limits measures fail, yet 
I believe that the Citizen Congress Act is a step in the 
right direction in regards to congressional reform.  I 
understand that Members of Congress work hard and are 
very busy, but I also believe Congress needs to truly 
reidentify with the voters of this country.  I ask that 
you pledge support for this measure, and I look forward
to your reply.

Sincerely,
</textarea>
<p>
