<head>
<TITLE>DRUG BROCHURE</TITLE>
</head>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<P align=center>
<img src="/empower/surge.jpg"></P>
<P>
<center>
<I>"Since 1992, the nation has suffered the greatest<br>
increase in drug use and the largest expansion in<br>
the supply of illegal drugs ever measured . . ."</i>
<P><blockquote>
<TABLE><tr><td col width=400>
Between 1980 and 1992, casual drug use in America declined sharply.  Strong presidential leadership helped cut casual drug use in half between 1977-1992, and reduced the number of cocaine users from almost 3 million in 1988 to 1.3 million in 1992.
<P>
Since 1992, however, a sustained, intelligent and integrated anti-drug effort has been largely abandoned.  The results are not surprising:  the last four years have brought the greatest increase in teen drug use ever measured.  Consider the facts:
<P>
Illicit drug use is soaring among Americas young people.  Overall use of drugs among 12-17 year olds rose 105 percent between 1992 and 1995.  Fully 2.42 million youths ages 12-17 use drugs on a monthly basis.
<P>
<img src="/empower/marijuana.jpg"><br>
<font size="1">Source: Monitoring the Future Survey, University of Michigan, 1996.</font>
</td>
<td valign=top col width=400><blockquote>Overall teen use of "hard drugs" and marijuana has skyrocketed.  Between 1992 and 1995, monthly LSD use jumped almost 200 percent, and marijuana use more than doubled.
<P>
<P align=center><img src="/empower/illicit.jpg">
<font size="1">Source: National Household Survey on Drug Abuse, Sept.1995.</font></P>
<P>
Marijuana use functions as the "gateway" to hard drugs.  According to the Center on Addiction and substance Abuse (CASA), teens who use marijuana are 85 times more likely to "graduate" to cocaine than those who abstain.  As CASA director, Joseph Califano noted, "The jump in marijuana use among Americas children from 1992-94 signals that 820,000 more of these children will try cocaine in their lifetime . . . Of that number, about 58,000 will become regular users and cocaine a ddicts.</blockquote></td></tr>
</TABLE>
<blockquote><P>
<a href="/empower/drug-abandon.html">Next Page</a>
<P>
</BODY>
<p><br>
